You're logged onto a cloud instance working on a problem with your fellow devs.
You want to invite them to log in and take a look at these crazy log messages.
What do? Oh. You have to ask them to cat their public SSH key,
paste it into IRC (wait, no, it's id\_rsa.pub, not id\_rsa silly!)
then you copy it and cat it to the end of authorized\_hosts.
That's where ssh-import-id comes in. With ssh-import-id,
you can add the public SSH keys from a trusted online identity to grant access.
Currently supported identities include Github and Launchpad.
